product-name: "Tesco Mobile Apple iPhone 5S 32GB iOS7 - Space Grey"
product-description: "\nA chip with 64-bit architecture. A fingerprint identity sensor. A better, faster camera. And an operating system built specifically for 64-bit. Any one of these features in a smartphone would make it ahead of its time. All of these features in a smartphone make it an iPhone that's definitely ahead of its time. iPhone 5s is precision crafted down to the micron. And it's evident throughout. The beautiful aluminum housing. The sleekness of metal and glass. Sapphire crystal in the Home button. And more sapphire crystal protecting the iSight camera. Design and construction of this level is unmatched. As a result, iPhone 5s looks and feels unbelievably thin and light. You check your iPhone dozens and dozens of times a day, probably more. Entering a passcode each time just slows you down. But you do it because making sure no one else has access to your iPhone is important. With iPhone 5s, getting into your phone is faster, easier, and even a little futuristic. Introducing Touch ID - a new fingerprint identity sensor. Put your finger on the Home button, and just like that your iPhone unlocks. It's a convenient and highly secure way to access your phone. Your fingerprint can also approve purchases from iTunes Store, the App Store, and the iBooks Store, so you don't have to enter your password. And Touch ID is capable of 360-degree readability. Which means no matter what its orientation - portrait, landscape, or anything in between - your iPhone reads your fingerprint and knows who you are. And because Touch ID lets you enroll multiple fingerprints, it knows the people you trust, too\n"

product-description: "\nThe iPhone 6 isn't simply bigger...it's better in every way. Larger yet thinner, more powerful and efficient, the innovative smartphone features a smooth metal surface that seamlessly meets the new Retina HD display. Designed with both hardware and software that function in perfect unison, the new generation of iPhone exceeds all expectations. Developing an iPhone with a larger, more advanced display pushed the edge of design. Every detail was carefully considered to enhance your experience. The first thing you will notice, when holding the iPhone 6, is how great it feels in your hand. The cover glass curves down around the sides to meet the anodised aluminium enclosure in this remarkable yet simplified design. By creating the iPhone 6 and iOS 8 together, Apple has optimised the software to enhance the physical design. iOS swipe gestures were designed to be more fluid across the seamless form, making it easy and enjoyable to navigate through your iPhone with one hand. With new features like Reachability you can interact with the larger screen in different ways too; simply double touch the Home button and the entire screen shifts down closer to your thumb. The buttons of the iPhone 6 were also redesigned for easy use; elongated volume buttons are integrated into the thinner profile, outlined to make them effortless to find by touch. The sleep/wake button has a new home on the side of the device to put it comfortable within reach. The size of the new, high-resolution Retina HD display on the iPhone 6 delivers high contrast, dual-domain pixels for more accurate colour at wider viewing angles, and an improved polariser making it one of the most advanced multi-touch displays Apple have ever made. The iPhone 6 is equipped with an iSight camera that houses a new sensor for life-like photos and videos. With Focus Pixels and new video features, like 1080p HD at 60fps, slo-mo at 240fps and time-lapse video mode, this iPhone caters for every budding photographer. Security is essential, which is why Apple have designed the breakthrough Touch ID feature. This technology lets you securely access your iPhone with the perfect password: your fingerprint. You can also use it to approve purchases from iTunes, iBooks and the App Store without having to enter your password. Built on 64-bit desktop-class architecture, the iPhone's A8 chip delivers more power, even while driving a larger display. product-description: "\nThe Samsung Galaxy S5 Neo is a super advanced smartphone with a 5.1" Full HD Super AMOLED screen.  Packed with innovative features, picture-in-picture technology lets you watch HD video while sending an email or text simultaneously. Samsung's easy-to-use S-Voice feature enables you to control the phone's functions by voice command. Capture the moment with the Galaxy S5 Neo's built-in 16-megapixel camera. This high powered camera enables you to take impromptu photos wherever you go, complete with a range of different features and functions to amaze a photography enthusiast. Features including Auto Focus ensure that you don't miss the action whereas HDR technology can be turned on when there is a strong counterlight or when the subject is shaded for brighter and vivid captures. Share your favourite images with friends and family via Samsung's Buddy Photo-share function. The Samsung Galaxy S5 Neo also supports a healthier lifestyle thanks to its built-in Heart Rate Sensor. This innovative feature follows your every beat using a sensor at the back of the handset; simply place your finger on the back of the Galaxy S5 Neo and measure your heart rate. The Galaxy S5 Neo also features the S-Health application that leads you through your fitness routines daily and consistently. Simply set your goals and achieve them with the help of the smartphone's built-in pedometer and S Health's constant tracking of your condition, walking distance, calories, speed, duration and more. A 2.5GHz quad-core processor powers the Samsung Galaxy S5 Neo with the intuitive Android 5.1 (Lollipop) operating system pre-installed.  The handset comes supplied with rechargeable lithium-ion battery, travel adaptor, data link cable, stereo headset and quick start guide. This mobile phone is unlocked to all networks and sold without a SIM so you can use your existing SIM card or choose a new SIM Only plan at www.tesco.com/phoneshop.\n"

product-name: "Apple iPhone 6 128GB iOS8 - Silver"
product-description: "\niPhone 6 isn't simply bigger - it's better in every way. Larger, yet dramatically thinner. More powerful, but remarkably power efficient. With a smooth metal surface that seamlessly meets the new Retina HD display. It's one continuous form where hardware and software function in perfect unison, creating a new generation of iPhone that's better by any measure. Developing an iPhone with a larger, more advanced display meant pushing the edge of design. From the seamless transition of glass and metal to the streamlined profile, every detail was carefully considered to enhance your experience. So while its display is larger, iPhone 6 feels just right. It's one thing to make a bigger display. It's something else entirely to make a bigger Multi-Touch display with brilliant colours and higher contrast at even wider viewing angles. But that's exactly what we did with the new Retina HD display. Built on 64-bit desktop-class architecture, the new A8 chip delivers more power, even while driving a larger display. The M8 motion coprocessor efficiently gathers data from advanced sensors and a new barometer. And with increased battery life, iPhone 6 lets you do more, for longer than ever. More people take more photos with iPhone than with any other camera. And now the iSight camera has a new sensor with Focus Pixels and new video features, like 1080p HD at 60 fps, slo-mo at 240 fps, and time-lapse video mode. So you'll have more reasons to capture more moments on video, too. iPhone 6 has faster LTE download speeds,* and it supports more LTE bands than any other smartphone so you can roam in more places. And when connected to Wi-Fi, you'll get up to 3x faster speeds. The breakthrough Touch ID technology lets you securely access your iPhone with the perfect password: your fingerprint. You can also use it to approve purchases from iTunes, iBooks, and the App Store without having to enter your password.\n"

product-name: "Apple iPhone 6 128GB iOS8 - Gold"
product-description: "\niPhone 6 isn't simply bigger - it's better in every way. Larger, yet dramatically thinner. More powerful, but remarkably power efficient. With a smooth metal surface that seamlessly meets the new Retina HD display. It's one continuous form where hardware and software function in perfect unison, creating a new generation of iPhone that's better by any measure. Developing an iPhone with a larger, more advanced display meant pushing the edge of design. From the seamless transition of glass and metal to the streamlined profile, every detail was carefully considered to enhance your experience. So while its display is larger, iPhone 6 feels just right. It's one thing to make a bigger display. It's something else entirely to make a bigger Multi-Touch display with brilliant colours and higher contrast at even wider viewing angles. But that's exactly what we did with the new Retina HD display. Built on 64-bit desktop-class architecture, the new A8 chip delivers more power, even while driving a larger display. The M8 motion coprocessor efficiently gathers data from advanced sensors and a new barometer. And with increased battery life, iPhone 6 lets you do more, for longer than ever. More people take more photos with iPhone than with any other camera. And now the iSight camera has a new sensor with Focus Pixels and new video features, like 1080p HD at 60 fps, slo-mo at 240 fps, and time-lapse video mode. So you'll have more reasons to capture more moments on video, too. iPhone 6 has faster LTE download speeds,* and it supports more LTE bands than any other smartphone so you can roam in more places. And when connected to Wi-Fi, you'll get up to 3x faster speeds. The breakthrough Touch ID technology lets you securely access your iPhone with the perfect password: your fingerprint. You can also use it to approve purchases from iTunes, iBooks, and the App Store without having to enter your password.\n"
